++- Bake the trust-root pubkey (TRUST_ROOT_ARMORED) + pinned fingerprint
++  (PINNED_FP) as constants in web/lib/gpg_verify_bundle.ts. Both are PUBLIC
++  by design (docs/carney_secret_inventory.md #1: "Public key may stay
++  published"). This eliminates the iter-1 P1 CWD lookup AND the production
++  docker file-copy problem in one move. Rotation now requires updating two
++  constants + a redeploy.
++- Install gnupg in the runner stage of web/Dockerfile (`apk add --no-cache
++  gnupg` — provides both gpg and gpgv on Alpine) so the server verifier path
++  actually has the binaries it needs.
++- Added an `error` listener on the spawn("gpg", ...) call so a missing gpg
++  is a controlled downgrade to present_unverified, never an unhandled
++  process throw.
++
++P3 stale comments cleaned: scripts/build_canonical_demo_bundle.py docstring
++no longer says "Signature: NONE"; web/app/runs/[runId]/audit/page.tsx header
++now describes the tri-valued state + CI guard instead of "pending sovereign
++signing"; .github/workflows/web_ci.yml comments describe the gpgv flow
++instead of the older GNUPGHOME/no-use-keyboxd approach.
